  <description type="morphology">Stems few to many in clumps, often glabrous basally, viscid-pubescent or ± scabrous
        distally. Leaf blades 1–4.5 × 0.4–3.5 cm. Inflorescences ± thyrselike, often narrow;
        involucres in clusters on short branches along main axis after first few dichotomous
        branches, 5–9 mm; bracts 30–70% connate, lobes ovate or ovate-oblong, base often 50–70% of
        height, apex obtuse or acute. Flowers: perianth usually pink, lavender, or magenta, rarely
        white. Fruits dark to pale gray-brown and mottled with dark gray-brown, tan, or red-brown,
        sometimes also faintly and irregularly pale striped, ovoid, 3–5 × 2.7–3.7 mm.</description>
